{{Quote|I was in the right place at the right time. That's happened a couple times in my life. But to have worked on the first ''Star Wars'' with George Lucas is something I'll always be proud of.|Anthony Forrest|<ref name="Let Me See">{{InsiderCite|216|Let Me See Your Identification}}</ref>}}
'''Anthony Forrest''' played [[Laze Loneozner/Legends|Fixer]] in scenes deleted from [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="Making of" /> He also contributed the physical performance of the [[Wanten|stormtrooper]] who was [[Mind trick|mind-tricked]] by [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] at the [[Mos Eisley]] roadblock;<ref name="Celebration Chicago">{{SW|url=news/billy-dee-williams-alan-tudyk-star-wars-celebration-chicago|text=Billy Dee Williams, Alan Tudyk Announced for Celebration Chicago}}</ref> the character's lines were voiced by [[Terrence Carson|Terry Carson]].<ref name="Sounds of SW">''[[The Sounds of Star Wars]]''</ref>

